Nigeria’s leading disinfectant and consumer bleach producer, HYPO, has intensifies its awareness campaign by taking its sensitisation programmes to worship centers and markets Lagos, pledging to support communities and family hygiene. Speaking at the Sensitization and Hygiene talk interactive session with the theme; ‘How to Prevent Corona virus, DisinfectwithHypo’ at the Ikeja Central Mosque in Lagos, the company’s Area Marketing Manager, Mr. Adetunji Aderinto, remarked that they embarked on the Sensitization exercise was to educate families and end-users on the need to disinfect their homes, surroundings and place of work. He added that individuals must be health conscious and avoid the rapid transfer of Coronavirus. He added that HYPO had several meetings and health engagement programmes with Nigeria Centre for Disease Control to sensitize and prevent the outbreak of the epidemic virus. Aderinto affirmed that they made public outreach to market places, worship centres and Primary Health Care Centres for community dialogues. He said, “The Federal Ministry of Health with other parastatals and agencies had meetings and Sensitization talk to create awareness with the Nigerian people on the need to prevent the Corona virus by ensuring that homes and places of doing businesses are properly sanitized from the intractable virus. Reacting to the donation, The Chief Imam of Ikeja Central Mosque, Alhaji AbdulRaheem Ajao, thanked Hypo for the community action programmes driven by their actionable policies to sanitize Nigerian homes. He said, HYPO has fulfilled its obligation to the Nigerian people by ensuring that every home is properly sanitized. 